<section class="si-features">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="feature rise" data-rise>
      <div class="copy">
        <h2>One project history for the team</h2>
        <p>
          By the end of commissioning, copies of the program usually live
          scattered on laptops and USB drives.
        </p>
        <p>
          Spyke gives the team one shared place for every saved version,
          with who added it, when, and a short note on why. Anyone on the
          project can open it and see where things stand.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="visual projhist" role="img" aria-label="A Spyke project card listing recent saved versions: v42 Retune PID loop, updated 2 hours ago by MK; v41 Add guard interlock, updated 1 day ago by JR; v40 Split infeed routine, updated 3 days ago by MK.">
        <div class="ph-head">Spyke</div>
        <div class="ph-list" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="ph-row"><span class="ph-v">v42</span><span class="ph-msg">Retune PID loop</span><span class="ph-when">2h ago</span><span class="ph-who">MK</span></div>
          <div class="ph-row"><span class="ph-v">v41</span><span class="ph-msg">Add guard interlock</span><span class="ph-when">1d ago</span><span class="ph-who">JR</span></div>
          <div class="ph-row"><span class="ph-v">v40</span><span class="ph-msg">Split infeed routine</span><span class="ph-when">3d ago</span><span class="ph-who">MK</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature flip rise" data-rise>
      <div class="copy">
        <h2>Review before handover</h2>
        <p>
          Before the customer gets the program, the team can walk through
          the differences together. Teammates comment on individual changes,
          question anything that looks off, and agree on the version being
          delivered.
        </p>
        <p>
          Engineers who were never on site can still take part in the review.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="visual">
        <div class="thread">
          <div class="mr-line">
            <span class="avatar" style="background:#0e7490">RD</span>
            <span class="bubble">Swapped the reset interlock on R12 — can you check it against the FAT spec?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mr-line me">
            <span class="avatar" style="background:#7c3aed">KV</span>
            <span class="bubble">Matches. One nit — add a note on the new debounce timer.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mr-verdict">
            <span class="pill green">✓ Approved</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature rise" data-rise>
      <div class="copy">
        <h2>Support after handover</h2>
        <p>
          When a customer calls a year later, the first question is whether
          the program still matches what you left behind. Export the program
          currently running at the site and compare it with the as-left
          version.
        </p>
        <p>
          Spyke shows whether the logic has changed since handover — and if
          it has, where to begin investigating.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="visual" role="img" aria-label="A Spyke structured-text diff of the program running on site against the as-left version: the infeed delay timer changed from 200 to 450 milliseconds.">
        <div class="st-diff" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="st-line">  ConvRun := StartPB AND NOT EStop;</div>
          <div class="st-line del">- InfeedDelay := T#200ms;</div>
          <div class="st-line add">+ InfeedDelay := T#450ms;</div>
          <div class="st-line">  RejectPulse := T#80ms;</div>
          <div class="st-line">  Ready := ConvRun AND Homed;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
